definition: to anticipate correctly the intentions or actions of : outguess
to analyze or figure out (something, such as a problem or course of action)
examples: I psyched it all out by myself and decided

definition: to make psychologically uneasy : intimidate, scare
examples: has a way of psyching out the competition

definition: to make (someone, such as oneself) psychologically ready especially for performance
examples: psyched herself up for the race
